@bizarro12345 So, it’s not mandatory to rename obs64.exe to something else, like ShellHost.exe, right? Also, I’ve already modified the details of obs64.exe so that it appears to be a Microsoft application.

@null I’ve already tried remote access, but the connection keeps dropping. When I open the link on my PC, the stream works fine, but when I open it from another device, like my phone, the connection gets interrupted. I figured out this happens because of the internet connection, since it’s sending around 12–20 Mbps. Is there a way to compress the streaming video, like OBS does?

@bizarro12345 Also, I noticed a bug: even though the “copy video URL,” “room ID,” and “chat room” buttons show that the content has been copied, when I try to paste, nothing is actually there (no link, etc.).

@null  If I stream the Evadus+ screen via OBS Studio (i rename it to "something".exe and run it not in "VM" but on my host pc) and have someone send me the answers through facebook/messenger will be detected on Respondus? Do I need to rename obs.exe or not?

My idea is to run Evadus+ in full screen only when starting Respondus, then switch it to window mode and stream the screen. After that, I would open another browser or Evadus Lite and from there via facebook/messenger they will send me the answers.

Would this kind of setup be detectable? Is it 100% undetectable?
